  <occupancy><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard Rooms</strong> are around 14-20m². Some of the rooms are excavated into the limestone rocks, whilst other offer panoramic views. Each of the hotel’s rooms are individual and dotted about different levels of the Sassi, echoing back to their original configuration. The rooms and common spaces are connected by an internal lift. The living spaces are modernised but retain a sense of their ancient origins. The rooms are immersed in the atmosphere of the Sassi, decorated in a simple and fresh style with wooden furnishings. All rooms are equipped with heating / air conditioning, free wifi, TV, minibar an hairdryer. These rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Suites</strong> offer much more space at 50m². They each have a bedroom, large living room which has a double sofa bed, private bathroom and a private terrace with views across the Sassi. There rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><strong>Double Rooms for Single Use </strong>are available on request, please call to book. </p>]]></occupancy>
